snippet.textDisplay:
My take on it is that "The Search" was meant to be him finding whatever he was looking for.

He mentions "album 4" a lot in his older stuff and talks about how once he drops it things will change. He talks about how he will blow up from it.

"Lost" to me is basically saying that he didn't find whatever it was he was looking for from The Search, which is presume is inner peace, self love, and happiness.

But from the way he is bench pressing the balloons in this, I feel like he is at a point where he is proud of him progress and is making progress despite his critics.

So I expect Lost, if it's his next album, to have an overall theme of "do it for yourself" I also predict he will have a few songs (including this one) that will speak about the criticism he received
